# Data Patterns

## Query Helpers — `src/lib/db/queries/`

All database reads and writes must go through helper functions defined in `src/lib/db/queries/`. Never call the `db` client directly from server components or server actions.

Organize query files by domain (e.g. `decks.ts`, `cards.ts`):

```
src/lib/db/queries/
  decks.ts   ← all deck reads and writes
  cards.ts   ← all card reads and writes
```

Each helper is a plain async function that accepts typed inputs and handles auth scoping internally:

```ts
// src/lib/db/queries/decks.ts
import { db } from "@/lib/db/db";
import { decks } from "@/lib/db/schema";
import { eq, and } from "drizzle-orm";

export async function getDecksByUser(userId: string) {
  return db.select().from(decks).where(eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId));
}

export async function getDeckById(deckId: string, userId: string) {
  const [deck] = await db
    .select()
    .from(decks)
    .where(and(eq(decks.id, deckId), eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId)));
  return deck ?? null;
}

export async function createDeck(title: string, userId: string) {
  const [deck] = await db
    .insert(decks)
    .values({ title, clerkUserId: userId })
    .returning();
  return deck;
}
```

## Fetching — Server Components Only

All data reads must happen in async server components via query helpers. Never fetch from client components.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — client-side fetch
"use client";
useEffect(() => {
  fetch("/api/decks").then(...);
}, []);

// ❌ BAD — db client used directly in a server component
export default async function DecksPage() {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  const decks = await db.select().from(decks).where(eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId));
  return <DeckList decks={decks} />;
}

// ✅ GOOD — server component calls a query helper
import { getDecksByUser } from "@/lib/db/queries/decks";

export default async function DecksPage() {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  if (!userId) redirect("/sign-in");
  const decks = await getDecksByUser(userId);
  return <DeckList decks={decks} />;
}
```

## Mutations — Server Actions Only

All inserts, updates, and deletes must go through server actions that call query helpers. Never use API routes or client-side fetches for DB writes.

```ts
// ❌ BAD — db client used directly in a server action
"use server";
export async function createDeck(input: CreateDeckInput) {
  await db.insert(decks).values({ title: input.title, clerkUserId: userId });
}

// ✅ GOOD — server action delegates to a query helper
"use server";
import { createDeck } from "@/lib/db/queries/decks";

export async function createDeckAction(input: CreateDeckInput) {
  const validated = createDeckSchema.parse(input);
  const { userId } = await auth();
  if (!userId) throw new Error("Unauthorized");
  return createDeck(validated.title, userId);
}
```

## Validation — Zod Required

Every server action must validate its input with Zod before calling a query helper.

```ts
// ❌ BAD — no validation, FormData type
export async function createDeckAction(data: FormData) {
  await createDeck(data.get("title") as string, userId);
}

// ✅ GOOD — typed input, Zod validation
import { z } from "zod";

const createDeckSchema = z.object({
  title: z.string().min(1).max(100),
});

type CreateDeckInput = z.infer<typeof createDeckSchema>;

export async function createDeckAction(input: CreateDeckInput) {
  const validated = createDeckSchema.parse(input);
  const { userId } = await auth();
  if (!userId) throw new Error("Unauthorized");
  return createDeck(validated.title, userId);
}
```

## Rules

- All `db` calls live in `src/lib/db/queries/` — never call `db` directly from components or actions
- Server components fetch data via query helpers — no `useEffect`, no `fetch()` in client components
- Server actions mutate data via query helpers — no `/api/` routes for DB writes
- Always define a TypeScript type for server action inputs (use `z.infer<typeof schema>`)
- Never use `FormData` as a server action parameter type
- Always call `auth()` and validate ownership before any mutation (see clerk-auth rule)
